          "text": "Your LED circuit is ready! 🎉 Here's a summary of what was built:\n\n---\n\n### 🔴 LED Blink Circuit\n\n| Part | Details |\n|------|---------|\n| **LED** | Red LED on the breadboard |\n| **Resistor** | 220Ω (current-limiting) |\n| **Signal Pin** | Arduino **D13** → LED Anode |\n| **Ground** | LED Cathode → Resistor → GND |\n\n---\n\n### ⚙️ How it works\n- The **220Ω resistor** protects the LED from drawing too much current.\n- The Arduino sketch **blinks the LED** — 1 second ON, 1 second OFF — in a continuous loop.\n\n### 📝 Sketch Logic\n- `setup()` — Sets pin 13 as OUTPUT\n- `loop()` — Toggles the LED HIGH/LOW with 1-second delays\n\nWant to change the blink speed, LED color, or add more LEDs? Just ask!"
